In this role, the individual's focus will be to provide application support and technical solutions to material and metal handling challenges.
To be successful, candidates should have a good understanding of all areas of plant design, especially material handling, to analyze the client's current situation and work with the Magaldi team to develop engineering solutions.
This role is suitable for people who enjoy solving problems in the product development phase, Interfacing with Customers, and providing technical support to the production and sales department.
Position Title : Application Engineer
Experience : 5+ years of drafting manufacturing equipment and systems within industrial plants; Experience in Material Handling a plus.
Degree required : Associate or higher in drafting, mechanical technology/engineering, or related field. Additional work experience instead of an advanced degree(s) shall be considered.
CAD Capabilities : Very strong knowledge of 2D and 3D CAD drawing programs (Autocad & Inventor specifically), skills in sizing calculation and FEM analysis are a plus;
Certifications : AutoCAD and Inventor certifications are a plus
Other Software : Be proficient in the MS Office suite (Word, Excel, PPT, etc.), SAP, etc.
Field Measurements : Be able to accurately and efficiently take critical field measurements when needed
Travel : Average of approximately 20-30% to industrial customer sites after extensive training in Italy.
Language requirements : English. Spanish or Italian is considered a plus.
Responsibilities: | Provide customer layouts of Magaldi equipment, and in some cases, place Magaldi equipment within plant drawings;
Detail drawings, layout, bill of materials;
Complete mechanical design with traditional or FEM sizing;
Understanding of Technical Specifications and International Standards to design following internal/customer requirements;
Management of the relationship with the other functions and entities of the Group, in the definition of new solutions and best practices;
Technical reporting;
Commercial office support both in the USA and Italy in identifying technical and innovative solutions;
Perform field measurements and help guide solutions in coordination with the Italian Engineering team;
Help complete engineering orders for potential projects as they occur;
Write and proofread technical documentation as needed.

As a Senior Software Engineer, you'll spend your days translating requirements into solutions, writing code, collaborating with cross-functional teams and providing us with the insights necessary to think beyond the status quo.
You'll oversee small project teams consisting of other engineers who will look to you as a trusted advisor, a subject matter expert who provides guidance and the right tools to get the job done.
Assists in providing guidance to small groups of 5 to 6 engineers, including offshore associates, for assigned Engineering projects by proving pertinent documents, directions, examples, and timeline.
Provides support to the business by responding to user questions, concerns, and issues (for example, technical feasibility, implementation strategies); researching and identifying needed solutions; determining implementation designs; providing guidance regarding implications of new and enhanced systems; identifying short and long term solutions; and directing users to appropriate contacts for issues outside of associate's domain.
Manages small to large-sized complex projects by reviewing project requirements;
translating requirements into technical solutions;
researching and identifying alternative solutions;
determining needed solution based on return on investment and value add to the business;
gathering requested information (for example, design documents, product requirements, wire frames);
writing and developing code; conducting unit testing;
communicating status and issues to team members and stakeholders;
collaborating with project team and cross functional teams;
identifying areas of opportunity;
interpreting information and identifying a solution;
ensuring solution is sustainable across implementation and use;
troubleshooting open issues and bug-fixes;
and ensuring on-time delivery and hand-offs.
Troubleshoots business and production issues by gathering information (for example, issue, impact, criticality, possible root cause); performing root cause analysis to reduce future issues; engaging support teams to assist in the resolution of issues; developing solutions; driving the development of an action plan; performing actions as designated in the plan; interpreting the results to determine further action; and completing online documentation.
Participates in the discovery phase of small to medium-sized projects to come up with high level design by partnering with the product management, project management, business, and user experience teams.
Demonstrates up-to-date expertise and applies this to the development, execution, and improvement of action plans by providing expert advice and guidance to others in the application of information and best practices; supporting and aligning efforts to meet customer and business needs; and building commitment for perspectives and rationales.
Provides and supports the implementation of business solutions by building relationships and partnerships with key stakeholders; identifying business needs; determining and carrying out necessary processes and practices; monitoring progress and results; recognizing and capitalizing on improvement opportunities; and adapting to competing demands, organizational changes, and new responsibilities.
We are looking for someone that has experience in JAVA full stack, as well as strong REACT Native JavaScript-based framework.
Extensive understanding of Kubernetes, microservice architecture and design, and best practices around multithreading, networking, offline storage and performance tuning
Expert level knowledge and understanding of Java, Spring Boot, and experience working with distributed systems and teams.
Experience with refactoring/redesigning/rewriting existing applications is a plus (We are in the process of redesigning and refactoring of our current system)
Ability to build products with focus on testability, someone who loves test coverage (well versed with Mockito and JUnit)
A disciplined approach to development, code review, testing, documentation and code structure in a team environment.
A constant desire to improve, learn more and take things to the next level and a passion for adopting the latest features in Kubernetes, Java, and Spring Boot.
Demonstrated knowledge of core design patterns to integrate with internal and external entities and data sources building fault tolerant systems;
Designing and testing Relational Database Management Systems including DB2, MySQL, JDBS and NOSQL;
Implementing Coding Standards using tools such as Sonar and Jocaco; using Azure cloud( Or any cloud) in deploying the application on different servers and maintaining the application to its standards for the users; and experience with project life-cycle, including analysis, design, development, implementation, support and enhancement.
You come to the table with a comprehensive knowledge of JAVA as well as Agile methodologies.
You'll make an impact by... | Effectively translating requirements into project parameters while working with agility from cradle to grave.
Helping cross-functional teams to solve for business problems and develop solutions that enable us to redefine a "best-in-class" customer experience.
Encouraging the project teams that you oversee to work collaboratively and to aim for insight-driven outcomes.
Ability to design for fault tolerance and high availability.
Have proficient knowledge and experience with Kafka Queues, Cassandra, Solr, Elastic Search, SQL
Demonstrated knowledge of the following programming Languages: Java, Python, Bash, Spark (SQL, Streaming), Hadoop Map-Reduce experience. Build Manager (Maven), Distributed Version Control (GIT), Continuous Integration (Jenkins) experience.
Solid devops skills in troubleshooting live applications, assessing performance bottlenecks of applications running on Linux
Develop high performance and scalable solutions that extract, transform, and load big data.
Option 1: Bachelor's degree in computer science, computer engineering, computer information systems, software engineering, or related area and 3 years' experience in software engineering or related area.Option 2: 5 years' experience in software engineering or related area.
Master's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Computer Information Systems, Software Engineering, or related area and 1 year's experience in software engineering or related area.

Lead Software Engineer
Conceptualize, design, program, test, implement and deploy software applications using the appropriate documentation, processes, and quality standards utilizing expertise in Angular, .NET APIs and SQL.
Provide business and project expertise when collaborating with clients, IT resources, vendors, and other stakeholders to identify the user requirements, assess technologies, recommend, and implement technical solutions.
Work significant and/or unique issues where analysis of data requires the evaluation of intangibles and work on special projects as assigned.
Review, repair legacy code, and recommend best practices focused on software development languages including .NET, C#, SQL, crystal reports and JavaScript.
Lead four Agile Sprint Teams comprising of six members each to ensure timely and quality delivery of business prioritized items.
Maximize the parallel execution of duties, especially during code writing using .NET Core so that the disparate pieces like user interface can be developed simultaneously with the business logic layer.
Coach and impart knowledge regarding the business domain and link it to the technical skills to junior level employees.
Understand the strategic nature of the requirements through regular correspondence with the business partners and provide solutions that would help achieve those goals.
In connection with above duties, utilize experience in Software Development Life Cycle, database development (SQL Server), application development frameworks (.NET, Angular), data analysis and reporting, and modular application design.
In connection with above duties, also utilize experience Test Driven Development, customer interaction and team liaison, performance improvement of enterprise application, and information system processes.
In connection with above duties, also utilize experience in the following in the mortgage lending industry: developing and maintaining portals by leveraging knowledge of Angular v13, .NET Core 3, CSS3 and Microsoft SQL Server 2019; planning and delivery of business requirements using Azure DevOps boards and CI/CD pipelines; implementing performance monitoring using Azure AppInsights and building dashboard using Azure dashboards; interfacing multiple enterprise systems viz.
Salesforce, ServiceNow and Tableau to allow the data flow into the portals;
leveraging Azure functions and cloud SQL server managed instances to achieve scalable solutions;
implementing unit tests for UI applications using Karma to produce stable and testable code;
designing the architecture for the new application with Angular v13 as the application framework;
integrating the Single Sign On using Okta cloud platform, allowing users to login into the application using existing MFA solutions;
porting existing Web Forms based screens to modern tech stack comprising of Angular v13, .NET Core based APIs and ASP.NET MVC which helps business users to quickly make decisions on loans based on various loan parameters;
adding UX analytics capabilities in applications by integrating FullStory platform;
securing the applications by analyzing and fixing security vulnerabilities using Veracode platform, resulting in a secure and compliant system;
maximizing the parallel execution of duties, especially during code writing so that the disparate pieces like user interface can be developed simultaneously with the business logic layer;
and coordinating with four Agile Sprint Teams comprising of six members each to ensure timely and quality delivery of Business prioritized items.
Requires related degree, experience and skills. Part of employee referral program.

Job Purpose
Develop applications and provide 24/7 administration and support, including tracking, troubleshooting, provisioning software updates, repairs and maintenance support to Progress Rail’s IT systems users.
Key Job Elements | Provide technical support to assigned technical systems, including installation, tracking, maintenance, troubleshooting and updating;
Provides customer ticket support to assigned systems (e.g., security systems; server maintenance, upgrades and patches; remote configuration, Uptime Connect; Enterprise Application Administration, etc.);
Engages and interacts with system users to identify requirements and develop documents for the reporting needs of the business; engages with system users to troubleshoot and resolve issues;
Diagnoses, documents and resolves system issues;
Documents processes, development plans and requirements;
Provides application support, including bug fixes, errors, failures and miscellaneous fixes.
Advanced duties and responsibilities: | Escalates top priority, production-critical issues to appropriate support staff;
Makes recommendations of perceived solutions to potential problem areas and methods for improvement;
Performs other job-related duties as assigned.
Education / Training | Bachelor’s degree in a related IT field or an Associates IT degree and related certifications, plus more than 5 years professional experience would also qualify.
Qualifications And Experience | 3+ years of IT experience in a web application environment;
2+ years of experience and proficiency in app development and additional IT experience;
Experience developing and providing solutions to automate business process workflows in K2/Power apps using designers (K2 designer, Power apps)/development tools (CSS, AJAX, ASP.net, C+, Visual Studio, JQuery, Java, XML, HTML);
Development experience in K2 applications (Version 5.0 and above) or Microsoft Power apps;
Development experience in MS SQL Server (SQL queries and stored procedures).
Preferred Skills: | Web app development;
Demonstrated experience developing application customizations, interfaces and reports;
Detail oriented / sense of urgency / follow-through;
Ability to multi-task, work independently and efficiently;
Proven interpersonal and communication skills;
Ability to follow-up with internal/external customers on inquiries, requests and complaints;
Willingness to participate in international meetings during non-typical business hours;
Ability to perform with frequent interruptions and/or distractions;
Strong proficiency in web related programming languages (PHP/JS/HTML) as well as underlying systems and databases (Windows/Linux/Apache/Oracle/MySQL systems);
High degree of analytical skills and strong business systems background;
Advanced Windows and Linux Operating Systems experience;
International Tax knowledge and experience; preferred;
GAAP understanding;
MRP experience preferred;
ERP experience preferred;
Ability to adapt to frequent changes in workload and adjust priorities quickly as circumstances dictate;
Ability to speak multiple languages is a plus;
Willingness to travel as required.

**Responsibilities**
We are looking for an algorithm technical manager who is obsessed with customer experience and passionate about building systems to detect various risks that can sabotage platform trust.
**Responsibilities:** | * Work with a team to design and implement algorithms to detect and control risks/frauds in contents/products/sellers/creators;
* Collaborate with strategy team, product managers, policy team and ops team to help define products and drive initiatives from engineering viewpoints
**Qualifications**
Minimum Qualifications: | * Currently pursuing a Phd degree in Computer Science or a related technical field. Recent graduates are highly encouraged to apply!
* Final year or recent graduate with a background in Software Development, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or a related technical discipline;
* Must obtain work authorization in country of employment at the time of hire, and maintain ongoing work authorization during employment;
* An understanding or keen interest in machine learning, NLP, or computer vision;
* Familiarity with programming languages such as C\+\+, Python, Go, or Java.
**Preferred Qualifications:** | * Interest or experience in anti-fraud, anti-spam, platform-integrity, or similar fields would be a cherry on top;
* A profound sense of responsibility, coupled with exceptional communication and teamwork skills.
* Interacting and occasionally having unsupervised contact with internal/external clients and/or colleagues;
* Appropriately handling and managing confidential information including proprietary and trade secret information and access to information technology systems; and
* Exercising sound judgment.

Duties: Design, develop and implement software solutions.
Solve business problems through innovation and engineering practices.
Involved in all aspects of the Software Development Lifecycle including analyzing requirements, incorporating architectural standards into application design specifications, documenting application specifications, translating technical requirements into programmed application modules, and developing or enhancing software application modules.
Identify or troubleshoot application code-related issues.
Take active role in code reviews to ensure solutions are aligned to pre-defined architectural specifications.
Assist with design reviews by recommending ways to incorporate requirements into designs and information or data flows.
Participate in project planning sessions with project managers, business analysts, and team members to analyze business requirements and outline proposed solutions.
Minimum education and experience required: Master's degree in Applied Computer Science, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Computer Information Systems, Information Technology, Electronic Engineering, or related field of study plus 3 years (36 months) of experience in the job offered or as Software Engineer, IS Technical Specialist, Software Developer, IT Analyst, or related occupation.
The employer will alternatively accept a Bachelor's degree in Applied Computer Science, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Computer Information Systems, Information Technology, Electronic Engineering, or related field of study plus 5 years (60 months) of experience in the job offered or as Software Engineer, IS Technical Specialist, Software Developer, IT Analyst, or related occupation.
This position requires three (3\) years of experience with the following:
Developing applications throughout the entire development life cycle;
Creating Java web applications including client interactions, system design, interaction with Java EE application server, and web services utilizing Java Development including core Application Program Interfaces, web services, multithreaded concurrent programming, JSON, XML, design patterns, Service Oriented Architecture Pattern, Spring including Spring MVC, Spring data, and Spring Security, SOAP, and REST services;
Developing and implementing Microservices using Spring Boot and Event Driven architecture;
Developing builds using Maven pattern builds;
Implementing data models and defining tables, indexes, views, stored procedures and data-integrity constraints in relational Database Management platforms including Oracle and Object-Relational Database Management tools including Postgres;
Managing and querying data using SQL;
Building and maintaining Java web applications running on web application servers such as Apache Tomcat;
Deploying and operating in public cloud and automating deployments using Terraform or CI/CD pipelines;
Conducting application development using toolsets including Intellij, Jenkins, Postman, and Bruno;
Deploying applications using Jenkins, Jules and Jfrog artifactory;
Integrating and enterprise testing utilizing Wiremock, Hoverfly, Jmeter and Blazemeter;
Implementing scalable systems, release management, software configuration, design, and development;
Driving the software development life cycle by participating in requirements gathering, design reviews, coding, testing, deployment and maintenance;
Delivering products using Agile methodologies;
Testing at the unit, integration and system level and using testing frameworks including Cucumber, Selenium, and Junit and mock testing frameworks including EasyMock and Mockito;
Applying Object-Oriented design and patterns by leveraging patterns such as Factory, Strategy, Observer, or MVC to solve design challenges;
Aligning established application, data, and infrastructure architecture disciplines throughout every Software Development Life Cycle phase;
Supporting applications within a production environment using Grafana, Splunk and Dynatrace;
Conducting Application Performance assessment using tools including Jmeter;
Conducting business analysis \& continuous improvement by Identifying performance bottlenecks, refactor legacy code and implement enhancements to reduce technical debt.

TikTok’s Global E‑commerce Data Science team powers TikTok Shop by building analytical frameworks and product metrics to drive growth, improve operational efficiency, and optimize the buyer, seller, and creator experiences across regions.
They identify trends, user or merchant behavior patterns, and opportunities for business optimization through exploratory analysis and proactive insights generation.
The team designs and interprets A/B tests and causal experiments to inform product improvements for user growth, transaction funnels, and feature adoption.
They also develop dashboards and data pipelines that enable cross‑functional teams—Product, Operations, and Engineering—to monitor product performance and implement data-driven changes easily.
**Summer Start Dates:** | * May 11th, 2026
* May 18th, 2026
* May 26th, 2026
* June 8th, 2026
* June 22nd, 2026
**Responsibilities:** | * Analyze product usage and engagement data (e.g., retention, conversion, feature adoption) to identify trends and actionable insights;
* Support design and evaluation of A/B tests or feature experiments; compute lift, assess statistical significance, and help interpret outcomes;
* Conduct exploratory data analysis using SQL and Python to detect patterns, anomalies, or feature-driven behaviors;
* Create dashboards, visualizations, and summary reports to communicate findings to product, engineering, and design teams;
* Collaborate cross-functionally with product managers and engineers to implement metrics and iterate on insights; document analysis and methodologies.
Minimum Qualifications: | * Currently pursuing a PhD in Computer Science, Statistics, Econometrics, Mathematics or other quantitative disciplines;
* Proficient in data analysis tools and languages such as SQL, Python, or R;
* Practical experience with data querying and scripting languages (e.g. SQL, Python, R) and basic statistical/data analysis tools;
* Familiar with statistical modeling, A/B testing, or experiment design concepts, drawn from coursework, projects, or internships.
* Prior internship or project experience in product analytics, A/B testing, or data science roles;
* Strong communication, collaboration, and storytelling skills - able to translate technical findings into product recommendations.
The hourly rate range for this position in the selected city is $52\.25- $52\.25\.

Duties: Advise cross-functional teams on technology selection to achieve target state architecture and make decisions on improvements to current technologies.
Contribute to the development of technical methods in specialized fields in line with the latest product development methodologies.
Create reusable software frameworks that improve velocity and quality of output across teams and functions.
Create scalable data frameworks using appropriate software design.
Architect and implement enterprise solutions, including data and analytics platforms on cloud and on-premises services, preferably using AWS and Databricks, ensuring security, scalability, and compliance for ingestion, transformation, and consumption across structured and unstructured data sources.
Drive evaluation sessions with external vendors, startups, and internal teams to probe architectural designs, technical credentials, and applicability for use within existing systems and architecture.
Define product data architecture target state and drive strategy achievement.
Participate in data architecture governance bodies and evaluate recommendations for new technology, providing feedback.
Design secure and automated pipelines for ingestion patterns.
Support the implementation of enterprise-wide data governance frameworks and enforce access controls and lineage tracking.
Evaluate workforce-related use cases to build knowledge graphs, skill maps, and support advanced analytics, including system dependency mapping and workforce intelligence using graphs.
Produce and maintain technical documentation, including High-Level Design Documents and Architecture Decision Records.
Host architecture review board meetings, lead architecture review sessions, and participate in governance bodies to ensure adherence to enterprise standards.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including product managers, engineers, security, and compliance, to align data and solution architecture with business needs and ensure solutions meet compliance and regulatory requirements.
Contribute to architectural standards and communities of practice.
Mentor architects and engineers on systems, standards, and processes under architecture.
**Qualifications**
Minimum education and experience required: Bachelor's degree in Electronic Engineering or related field of study plus 7 years (84 months) of experience in the job offered or as Data Architect, Software Engineer, Project Engineer, or related occupation.
This position requires experience with the following:
Designing RESTful APIs using Azure API Management;
Architecting APIs and integrating them with serverless functions for scalable and robust application backends using Azure Functions;
Developing and deploying microservices using technologies such as Azure Kubernetes Service or Azure App Service;
Integrating SSO and IAM solutions to manage user access and policy enforcement across data platforms and third-party services;
Architecting hybrid data platform solutions using Azure and on-premises services to support large-scale transactional and analytics solutions;
Organizing architectural design reviews to align software components with enterprise architecture standards, ensuring scalability, security, resilience, and compliance;
Delivering system design, application development, testing, and operational stability, including enterprise architecture solutions;
Building data ingestion and transformation pipelines using Azure services such as Azure Blob storage, or Azure Data Factory;
Configuring CI/CD pipelines;
Designing both real-time, streaming and batch processing workloads;
Implementing data governance and privacy frameworks using RBAC , ABAC and data cataloging;
Exploring governance and workforce-related use cases with Neo4j;
Modeling relational, dimensional, and graph data models;
Modeling Kafka message topics;
Governing and integrating data from third- party services, vendor systems, and SaaS applications such as Workday or SAP S/4HANA, into data lake environments using a variety of ingestion methods, such as real-time streaming, API integration or SFTP file transfers;
Producing and maintaining architecture deliverables using HLDD, System architect Erwin data modelling tools, and Bizz design for architectural drawings;
Managing workstreams using agile project management methodologies.
This position requires the following certification(s): Architecture related Cloud certification such as AWS Certified Solutions Architect - Associate Microsoft Azure Fundamentals, or Microsoft Azure Data Fundamentals; TOGAF® 9; Enterprise design tools such as Bizz design Enterprise Studio® Certification or Erwin.
